urasian Customs Union]] (including [[Belarus]])\n** [[Eurasian Economic Union]] (including [[Belarus]])\n** [[Greater Mekong Subregion]]\n** [[Gulf Cooperation Council]] (GCC)\n** [[Union for the Mediterranean]] (including most [[Europe|European]] countries and some [[Africa|African]] countries)\n\n* ''by culture:''\n** [[Eastern world]]\n*** [[East Asian cultural sphere]]\n**** [[Greater China]]\n***** [[China proper]]\n****** [[Northern and southern China]]\n***** [[Manchuria]]\n***** [[Mongolian Plateau]]\n***** [[Tibet]]\n***** [[Xinjiang]]\n****** [[Dzungaria]]\n****** [[Tarim Basin]]\n**** [[Korea]]\n**** [[Nanyang (region)|Nanyang]]\n*** [[Greater India]] (aka the [[East Indies]])\n**** [[Farther India]]\n***** [[Malay world]]\n****** [[Greater Indonesia]]\n******* [[Nusantara]]\n**** [[Indian subcontinent]]\n** [[Muslim world]] (aka the [[Muslim world|Islamic world]])\n*** [[Arab world]]\n**** [[Mashriq]]\n\n* ''by religion:''\n** [[Abrahamic religions]] ([[Abrahamic religions|Western Asian religions]] or [[Western religions]])\n** [[Eastern religions]]\n*** [[Indian religions|Dharmic religions]] ([[Indian religions]])\n*** [[East Asian religions|Taoic religions]] ([[East Asian religions]] or [[East Asian religions|Far Eastern religions]])\n\n* ''by biogeography:''\n** [[Malesia]]\n\n===== [[Europe]] =====\n* ''by the United Nations Statistics Division's geoscheme (see also: [[United Nations geoscheme for Europe|UN geoscheme for Europe]]):''\n** [[Eastern Europe]] \u2013 the UN includes [[North Asia]] ([[Siberia]]) and part of [[Central Europe]] ([[Czech Republic|Czechia]], [[Hungary]], [[Poland]] and [[Slovakia]]) in this subregion\n** [[Northern Europe]] \u2013 the UN includes the [[British Isles]] and the [[Baltic states]] in this subregion\n** [[Southern Europe]] \u2013 the UN includes [[Slovenia]] ([[Central Europe]]) in this subregion\n** [[Western Europe]] \u2013 the UN includes part of [[Central Europe]] (the [[Geographical distribution of German speakers#DACH countries|DACH]] countries and [[Liechtenstein]]) in this subregion\n\n* ''by geography:''\n** [[Central and Eastern Europe]]\n** [[Central Europe]]\n** [[Eastern Europe]]\n** [[Baltic region|Northeastern Europe]]\n** [[Northern Europe]]\n*** [[Scandinavia]]\n** [[Northwestern Europe]]\n** [[Southern Europe]]\n*** [[Southeast Europe|Southeastern Europe]] (aka the [[Balkans]])\n*** [[Iberian Peninsula|Southwestern Europe]] (aka [[Iberian Peninsula|Iberia]])\n** [[:de:Westmitteleuropa|West-Central Europe]] {{in lang|de}}\n** [[Western Europe]]\n\n* ''by physiography:''\n** [[Balkans|Balkan Peninsula]]\n** [[British Isles]]\n*** [[Great Britain]]\n*** [[Hebrides]]\n*** [[Ireland]]\n*** [[Isle of Man]]\n*** [[Isle of Wight]]\n** [[Caucasus]]\n*** [[North Caucasus]]\n*** [[Transcaucasia|South Caucasus]] (aka [[Transcaucasia]])\n** [[Channel Islands]]\n*** [[Bailiwick of Guernsey|Guernsey]]\n*** [[Jersey]]\n** [[Eurasian Steppe]]\n** [[Fennoscandia|Fennoscandian Peninsula]]\n*** [[Kola Peninsula]]\n*** [[Scandinavian Peninsula]]\n** [[European Plain|Great European Plain]]\n*** [[East European Plain]]\n** [[Iberian Peninsula]]\n** [[Italian Peninsula]] (aka the [[Italian Peninsula|Apennine Peninsula]])\n** [[Mediterranean Basin]]\n\n* ''by geology:''\n** [[Alpine orogeny]]\n** [[East European craton]]\n*** [[Baltic Shield]]\n*** [[Ukrainian Shield]]\n\n* ''by geopolitics:''\n** [[East-Central Europe]]\n** [[Post-Soviet states]]\n*** [[Baltic states]]\n*** [[Commonwealth of Independent States]]\n**** [[Union State]]\n** [[Western world]]\n*** [[European Union]] (EU)\n*** [[NATO]]\n*** [[North Sea Commission]] (NSC)\n\n* ''by economics:''\n** [[Central European Free Trade Agreement]] (CEFTA)\n** [[Commonwealth of Independent States Free Trade Area]] (CISFTA) \u2013 including [[Armenia]] and most [[Central Asia|Central Asian]] countries\n** [[Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement]] (CETA) \u2013 including [[Canada]]\n** [[Europe, the Middle East and Africa|EMEA]] (including [[Africa]] and the [[Middle East]])\n** [[Eurasian Customs Union]] (EACU) \u2013 including [[Armenia]] and [[Kyrgyzstan]]\n** [[Eurasian Economic Union]] (EAEU) \u2013 including [[Armenia]] and [[Kyrgyzstan]]\n** [[European Economic Area]] (EEA) \u2013 including [[Cyprus]]\n** [[European Free Trade Association]] (EFTA)\n** [[European Single Market]] (including [[Cyprus]])\n** [[European Union Customs Union]] (EUCU) \u2013 including [[Cyprus]] and [[Turkey]]\n** [[European Union\u2013Turkey Customs Union]] (including [[Cyprus]] and [[Turkey]])\n** [[Eurozone]] (including [[Cyprus]])\n** [[North Sea Region]] (NSR)\n** [[Union for the Mediterranean]] (UfM) \u2013 including some [[Western Asia|Western Asian]] countries and some [[Africa|African]] countries\n** [[Union State]]\n\n* ''by culture:''\n** [[Balkans]]\n*** [[Balkans|Eastern Balkans]]\n*** [[Balkans|Western Balkans]]\n** [[Baltic states]]\n** [[Benelux]]\n*** [[Belgium]]\n*** [[Netherlands]]\n*** [[Luxembourg]]\n** [[Mediterranean Basin|Mediterranean Region]]\n** [[Nordic countries]]\n** [[North Sea Region]]\n** [[S\u00e1pmi]], since 1809 divided between [[Finland]] and [[Sweden]]\n** [[Scandinavia]]\n** [[Visegr\u00e1d Group]]\n\n* ''by language:''\n** [[Germanic-speaking Europe]]\n*** [[List of territorial entities where German is an official language|DACH]]\n**** [[Germany]] ([[Germany|Deutschland]])\n**** [[Austria]]\n**** [[Switzerland]] ([[Switzerland|Confoederatio Helvetica]])\n** [[Languages of Europe#Romance|Romance-speaking Europe]] (aka [[Languages of Europe#Romance|Latin Europe]])\n** [[Slavic languages#Branches|Slavic-speaking Europe]]\n\n* ''by religion:''\n** [[Eastern religions]]\n*** [[Indian religions]]\n**** [[Buddhism in Europe]] ([[Kalmykia]])\n** [[Western religions]] ([[Abrahamic religions]] or [[Abrahamic religions|Western Asian religions]])\n*** [[Christianity]]\n**** [[Catholic Church]]\n**** [[Eastern Orthodox Church]]\n**** [[Protestantism]]\n*** [[Islam in Europe]]\n